That the verses between 563 and 567, since lost and therefore absent from the archetype, were 9 in number is a conjecture based on the common assumption of a leaf of 44 lines; but that some verses have been lost at that point is certain* They contained Eudoxus' division of the distance between the poles into 30 parts, without which the following verses 567—593 would have been unintelligible. Why they exist no more, which of many possible accidents swept them away, there is no means of determining.
